This archive contains two programs for use on the iLab.

client - a sample client demonstrating a possible user agent
raw - a test client that allows you to send raw protocol messages and 
      observe the respose from your server


Usage:
    client <name> <host> <port>

Will connect to the chat server at host:port and attempt to join the chat
using the given name. (We rely on the server to validate names.)

Once running, client will print incoming messages from the server, using
formatting and indentation to distinguish (1) messages sent by the
server itself, (2) private messages from other users, (3) general messages
sent by other users, and (4) errors sent by the server.

To send a regular message, type it and press enter.

To set your status, type /<status>

To query all users and their statuses, type ?
To query a specific user, type ?<name>

To send a private message to a user, type @<name> <message>
